➜Bronze horse head sculpture returned to China's Old Summer Palace
http://www.sohu.com/a/436054091_162758	39951
<p align="center"><img src="http://p1.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20201203/a6bd8dcdf4c0462ca89a686f0ef47498.jpeg" /></p>
<p align="justify">A bronze horse head sculpture, a treasure of China's Old Summer Palace, missing since the Anglo-French allied forces' looting 160 years ago, now returned to its original location in Beijing, capital of China, Dec. 1, 2020. It is the first time ever that a lost important cultural relic from the Old Summer Palace, also known as "Yuanmingyuan", has been returned to and housed at its original place after being repatriated from overseas. (Chen Xiaogen/Guangming Picture)</p>
